{"word":"ἐκκαλέω","slug":"ἐκκαλέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκκαλέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>έσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to call out</i> or <i>forth, summon forth</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to call out to oneself</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to call forth, elicit</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to call on</i> one <i>to</i> do, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}